Renegade tribesmen have surrounded some 300 soldiers, government officials and their families sheltering at a paramilitary fort in the town of Bugti, some 245 kilometres (152 miles) southeast of Quetta, since.
Last a barrage of rockets fired at Bugti killed up to 30 people including 18 Hindus and eight paramilitary soldiers.
Frontier Corps troops returned fire, but it wasn't known if the attackers suffered any casualties.
Paramilitary troops and tribal rebels have been locked in a standoff in the town of Dera Bugti, near Sui, since a violent clash on March 17 left dozens of civilians and eight troops dead.
